{"title_page": "Erasmus+", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=March 2014}}\n[[File:Erasmus+ Logo.svg|thumb|Logo of Erasmus+]]\n\n'''Erasmus+''' is the [[European Commission|European Commission's]] Programme for education, training, youth and sport for the period 2014\u20132020, succeeding the previous Lifelong Learning Programme (2007\u20132014). As an integrated programme, Erasmus+ offers more opportunities for mobility of learners and staff and cooperation across the education, training and youth sectors and is easier to access than its predecessors, with simplified funding rules and a structure which aims to streamline the administration of the programme.<ref name=\"programme\">[http://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/index_en.htm European Commission: Erasmus+]</ref>\n\n==Introduction==\nThe Programme is open to students, apprentices, teachers, lecturers, young people, volunteers, youth workers and people working in grassroots' sport. Approximately two-thirds of the budget is allocated to learning opportunities abroad for individuals, within the EU and beyond; the remainder will support partnerships between educational institutions, youth organisations, businesses, local and regional authorities and NGOs, as well as reforms to modernise education, training and youth systems.<ref name=\"pressrelease\">[http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-13-1110_en.htm Erasmus+ Press Release]</ref>\n\n==Jean Monnet Chairs==\nJean Monnet Chairs are teaching posts with a specialisation in European Union studies for university professors or senior lecturers.\nJean Monnet Chairs can:\n* enhance the teaching of EU studies at your institution through the curriculum\n* conduct, monitor and supervise research on EU matters at all education levels\n* be a mentor and advisor to the next generation of teachers and researchers\n* provide expert guidance to future professionals about European matters\nJean Monnet Chairs are encouraged to:\n* publish books within their university press during the grant period. The grant will cover part of the publication and, if need be, part of the translation costs\n* participate in dissemination and information events in your country and around Europe\n* organise events (lectures, seminars, workshops, etc.) with policymakers, civil society and schools\n* network with other academics and institutions supported by Jean Monnet\n* apply open educational resources, and publish the summaries, content, schedule and expected outcomes of your activities\n\nJean Monnet chairs have been established, for example, at the following universities (alphabetically): \n\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Augsburg]] ([[Christoph Vedder]])\n* [[Freie Universit\u00e4t Berlin]] (Tanja A. B\u00f6rzel)\n*[[Ruhr-Universit\u00e4t Bochum]] (Sebastian Bersick)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Bremen]] (Ulrike Liebert)\n* [[Technische Universit\u00e4t Chemnitz]] (Matthias Niedobitek)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Duisburg-Essen]] (Michael Kaeding und Ansgar Belke)<ref>[https://www.makro.wiwi.uni-due.de Lehrstuhl f\u00fcr Volkswirtschaftslehre]</ref>\n* [[Europa-Universit\u00e4t Viadrina]] (Matthias Pechstein)\n* [[Justus-Liebig-Universit\u00e4t Gie\u00dfen]] (Mahulena Hofmann)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Hamburg]] (Gabriele Clemens)\n* [[Ruprecht-Karls-Universit\u00e4t Heidelberg]] (Peter-Christian M\u00fcller-Graf)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Hildesheim]] (Michael Gehler)\n* [[Friedrich-Schiller-Universit\u00e4t Jena]] (Matthias Ruffert)<ref> {{Webarchiv|text=Friedrich-Schiller-Universit\u00e4t Jena |url=http://www.rewi.uni-jena.de/Prof_+Dr_+Matthias+Ruffert_p_89722-path-31803,31801,70773.html |wayback=20120825235351 |archiv-bot=2018-04-17 01:49:10 InternetArchiveBot }}</ref>\n*Hochschule f\u00fcr \u00d6ffentliche Verwaltung Kehl (Annegret Eppler)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Konstanz]] (Daniel Thym)<ref>{{Webarchiv|url=http://www.jura.uni-konstanz.de/thym/lehrstuhl-fuer-oeffentliches-recht-europarecht-und-voelkerrecht/ |wayback=20150518102822 |text=Universit\u00e4t Konstanz |archiv-bot=2019-04-19 02:43:58 InternetArchiveBot }}</ref>\n* [[Deutsche Sporthochschule K\u00f6ln]] (J\u00fcrgen Mittag)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t zu K\u00f6ln]] ([[Wolfgang Wessels]])\n* [[Otto-von-Guericke-Universit\u00e4t Magdeburg]] ([[Wolfgang Renzsch]])\n* [[Johannes-Gutenberg-Universit\u00e4t Mainz]] (Arne Niemann)\n* [[Carl-von-Ossietzky-Universit\u00e4t Oldenburg]] ([[Martin Heidenreich]])\n*[[Universit\u00e4t Osnabr\u00fcck]] (Jean Monnet Centre of Excellence in European Studies)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Paderborn]] (Dieter Krimphove)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Passau]] (Daniel G\u00f6ler)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Regensburg]] (Rainer Arnold)\n* [[Eberhard Karls Universit\u00e4t T\u00fcbingen]] (Rudolf Hrbek und Gabriele Abels)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t des Saarlandes]] ([[Thomas Giegerich]])\n* [[Bergische Universit\u00e4t Wuppertal|Universit\u00e4t Wuppertal]] (Hans J. Lietzmann) \n* [[Julius-Maximilians-Universit\u00e4t W\u00fcrzburg]] ([[Gisela M\u00fcller-Brandeck-Bocquet]])\n*\n\n== Erasmus+ for Education Staff ==\n'''Erasmus+ key action 1''' provides a unique opportunity for teachers, headmasters, trainers and other staff of education institutions to participate in international training courses in different European countries.\n\nSchools, universities, vocational education and training and adult education organizations are all eligible to receive full funding to attend [...]  courses under a KA1 mobility grant.\n\nThe Erasmus+ KA1 grant covers all the costs to attend [...] teacher training courses including travel, subsistence and course fee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.erasmustrainingcourses.com/teacher-training-courses-erasmus-plus-funding.html|title=Erasmus Plus Funding for Teacher Training Courses {{!}} Erasmus+ KA1|website=TEACHER TRAINING|access-date=2017-11-05}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==See also==\n* [[Erasmus Mundus]]\n* [[TEMPUS]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/ Erasmus+ Programme website]\n\n[[Category:European Commission projects]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=March 2014}}\n[[File:Erasmus+ Logo.svg|thumb|Logo of Erasmus+]]\n'''Erasmus+''' is the [[European Commission|European Commission's]] Programme for education, training, youth and sport for the period 2014\u20132020, succeeding the previous Lifelong Learning Programme (2007 - 2014). As an integrated programme, Erasmus+ offers more opportunities for mobility of learners and staff and cooperation across the education, training and youth sectors and is easier to access than its predecessors, with simplified funding rules and a structure which aims to streamline the administration of the programme.<ref name=\"programme\">[http://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/index_en.htm European Commission: Erasmus+]</ref>\n\n==Introduction==\nThe Programme is open to students, apprentices, teachers, lecturers, young people, volunteers, youth workers and people working in grassroots' sport. Approximately two-thirds of the budget is allocated to learning opportunities abroad for individuals, within the EU and beyond; the remainder will support partnerships between educational institutions, youth organisations, businesses, local and regional authorities and NGOs, as well as reforms to modernise education, training and youth systems.<ref name=\"pressrelease\">[http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-13-1110_en.htm Erasmus+ Press Release]</ref>\n\n==Jean Monnet Chairs==\nJean Monnet Chairs are teaching posts with a specialisation in European Union studies for university professors or senior lecturers.\nJean Monnet Chairs can:\n* enhance the teaching of EU studies at your institution through the curriculum\n* conduct, monitor and supervise research on EU matters at all education levels\n* be a mentor and advisor to the next generation of teachers and researchers\n* provide expert guidance to future professionals about European matters\nJean Monnet Chairs are encouraged to:\n* publish books within their university press during the grant period. The grant will cover part of the publication and, if need be, part of the translation costs\n* participate in dissemination and information events in your country and around Europe\n* organise events (lectures, seminars, workshops, etc.) with policymakers, civil society and schools\n* network with other academics and institutions supported by Jean Monnet\n* apply open educational resources, and publish the summaries, content, schedule and expected outcomes of your activities\n\nJean Monnet chairs have been established, for example, at the following universities (alphabetically): \n\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Augsburg]] ([[Christoph Vedder]])\n* [[Freie Universit\u00e4t Berlin]] (Tanja A. B\u00f6rzel)\n*[[Ruhr-Universit\u00e4t Bochum]] (Sebastian Bersick)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Bremen]] (Ulrike Liebert)\n* [[Technische Universit\u00e4t Chemnitz]] (Matthias Niedobitek)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Duisburg-Essen]] (Michael Kaeding und Ansgar Belke)<ref>[https://www.makro.wiwi.uni-due.de Lehrstuhl f\u00fcr Volkswirtschaftslehre]</ref>\n* [[Europa-Universit\u00e4t Viadrina]] (Matthias Pechstein)\n* [[Justus-Liebig-Universit\u00e4t Gie\u00dfen]] (Mahulena Hofmann)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Hamburg]] (Gabriele Clemens)\n* [[Ruprecht-Karls-Universit\u00e4t Heidelberg]] (Peter-Christian M\u00fcller-Graf)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Hildesheim]] (Michael Gehler)\n* [[Friedrich-Schiller-Universit\u00e4t Jena]] (Matthias Ruffert)<ref> {{Webarchiv|text=Friedrich-Schiller-Universit\u00e4t Jena |url=http://www.rewi.uni-jena.de/Prof_+Dr_+Matthias+Ruffert_p_89722-path-31803,31801,70773.html |wayback=20120825235351 |archiv-bot=2018-04-17 01:49:10 InternetArchiveBot }}</ref>\n*Hochschule f\u00fcr \u00d6ffentliche Verwaltung Kehl (Annegret Eppler)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Konstanz]] (Daniel Thym)<ref>{{Webarchiv|url=http://www.jura.uni-konstanz.de/thym/lehrstuhl-fuer-oeffentliches-recht-europarecht-und-voelkerrecht/ |wayback=20150518102822 |text=Universit\u00e4t Konstanz |archiv-bot=2019-04-19 02:43:58 InternetArchiveBot }}</ref>\n* [[Deutsche Sporthochschule K\u00f6ln]] (J\u00fcrgen Mittag)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t zu K\u00f6ln]] ([[Wolfgang Wessels]])\n* [[Otto-von-Guericke-Universit\u00e4t Magdeburg]] ([[Wolfgang Renzsch]])\n* [[Johannes-Gutenberg-Universit\u00e4t Mainz]] (Arne Niemann)\n* [[Carl-von-Ossietzky-Universit\u00e4t Oldenburg]] ([[Martin Heidenreich]])\n*[[Universit\u00e4t Osnabr\u00fcck]] (Jean Monnet Centre of Excellence in European Studies)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Paderborn]] (Dieter Krimphove)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Passau]] (Daniel G\u00f6ler)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t Regensburg]] (Rainer Arnold)\n* [[Eberhard Karls Universit\u00e4t T\u00fcbingen]] (Rudolf Hrbek und Gabriele Abels)\n* [[Universit\u00e4t des Saarlandes]] ([[Thomas Giegerich]])\n* [[Bergische Universit\u00e4t Wuppertal|Universit\u00e4t Wuppertal]] (Hans J. Lietzmann) \n* [[Julius-Maximilians-Universit\u00e4t W\u00fcrzburg]] ([[Gisela M\u00fcller-Brandeck-Bocquet]])\n*\n\n== Erasmus+ for Education Staff ==\n'''Erasmus+ key action 1''' provides a unique opportunity for teachers, headmasters, trainers and other staff of education institutions to participate in international training courses in different European countries.\n\nSchools, universities, vocational education and training and adult education organizations are all eligible to receive full funding to attend [...]  courses under a KA1 mobility grant.\n\nThe Erasmus+ KA1 grant covers all the costs to attend [...] teacher training courses including travel, subsistence and course fee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.erasmustrainingcourses.com/teacher-training-courses-erasmus-plus-funding.html|title=Erasmus Plus Funding for Teacher Training Courses {{!}} Erasmus+ KA1|website=TEACHER TRAINING|access-date=2017-11-05}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==See also==\n* [[Erasmus Mundus]]\n* [[TEMPUS]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/ Erasmus+ Programme website]\n\n[[Category:European Commission projects]]\n", "name_user": "Rosenborg BK Fan", "label": "safe", "comment": "Minor edit", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erasmus%2B"}
{"title_page": "Alessia Cara", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{short description|Canadian singer}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Alessia Cara\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Alessia Caracciolo\n| image            = Alessia Cara at the Capital Pride Concert.jpeg\n| caption          = Cara performing in 2018\n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1996|7|11}}<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbc.ca/radio/q/blog/12-things-you-need-to-know-about-alessia-cara-canada-s-first-ever-best-new-artist-grammy-winner-1.4509275 |title=12 things you need to know about Alessia Cara, Canada's first-ever best new artist Grammy winner |last=Van Evra |first=Jennifer |date=January 29, 2018 |publisher=[[CBC Radio]] |access-date=July 10, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Brampton]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| origin           = [[Brampton]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[alternative R&B]]\n* [[indie pop]]\n* [[Soul music|soul]]\n}}\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* songwriter\n* multi-instrumentalist\n}}\n| instrument       = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* guitar\n* ukulele\n* piano\n}}\n| years_active     = 2014\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[EP Entertainment|EP]]\n* [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]]<ref name=NYTimes19May>{{cite news|last1=Caramanica|first1=Jon|title=Alessia Cara Speaks Up for the Outsiders on 'Here'|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/20/arts/music/alessia-cara-speaks-up-for-the-outsiders-on-here.html|accessdate=June 1, 2015|newspaper=The New York Times|date=May 19, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Universal Music Canada]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/7767524/universal-music-canada-relocating-rock-star-building-toronto|title=Universal Music Canada Relocating To 'Rock Star Building' in Downtown Toronto|date=April 19, 2017|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n}}\n| associated_acts  = [[Pop & Oak]]\n| website          = {{URL|alessiacara.com}}\n| image_size       = 200px\n}}\n\n'''Alessia Caracciolo''' (born July 11, 1996), known professionally as '''Alessia Cara''' ({{IPAc-en|\u0259|'|l|\u025b|s|i|\u0259|_|'|k|\u0251\u02d0|r|\u0259|}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/a34453/celebrity-name-pronunciations/|title=11 Celeb Names You're Totally Pronouncing Wrong|work=[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]|date=July 31, 2017|accessdate=November 19, 2017}}</ref>), is a Canadian singer, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist.<ref name=\"teenvogue\">{{cite magazine|last1=Thurmond|first1=Alexandra|title=Sound Scout: Alessia Cara is the 18-year-old Singer-Songwriter We Cant Get Enough Of|url=http://www.teenvogue.com/entertainment/music/2015-05/sound-scout-alessia-cara-interview|accessdate=June 1, 2015|magazine=Teen Vogue|date=May 2015}}</ref><ref name=SPINTopPick>{{cite magazine|title=SPIN Singles Mix: Titus Andronicus, Vince Staples, Miguel, and More|url=http://www.spin.com/2015/05/singles-mix-titus-andronicus-vince-staples-miguel/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|magazine=SPIN Magazine|date=May 5, 2015}}</ref> After producing acoustic covers, she signed with [[EP Entertainment]] and [[Def Jam Recordings]] in 2014 and released her debut single the following year. \"[[Here (Alessia Cara song)|Here]]\" reached number 19 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] chart and was a [[sleeper hit]] in the United States, peaking at number 5 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart.<ref name=\"FaderCover\">{{cite magazine|last1=Zeichner|first1=Naomi|title=Every Introvert Needs To See This Song|url=https://www.thefader.com/2015/04/27/alessia-here|accessdate=May 12, 2015|magazine=The Fader|date=April 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Lewis|first1=Brittany|title=Alessia \"Here\" (New Music)|url=http://globalgrind.com/2015/04/28/alessia-here-new-music/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|publisher=Global Grind|date=April 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nCara's debut studio album, ''[[Know-It-All]]'' (2015), reached number 8 on the [[Canadian Albums Chart]] and number 9 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart in the United States. The album's third single, \"[[Scars to Your Beautiful]]\", reached number 8 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 in 2016. In 2017, Cara collaborated with DJ and producer [[Zedd]] to create the single \"[[Stay (Zedd and Alessia Cara song)|Stay]]\", and with rapper [[Logic (rapper)|Logic]] to feature in his song {{nowrap|\"[[1-800-273-8255 (song)|1-800-273-8255]]\"}}. Cara has received nominations for four [[Grammy Awards]], including a win for [[Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/grammys-2018-alessia-cara-wins-best-new-artist/|title=Grammys 2018: Alessia Cara Wins Best New Artist |website=Pitchfork.com|language=en|access-date=January 29, 2018}}</ref> She was nominated for [[Latin Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]] and [[Latin Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]] at the [[20th Annual Latin Grammy Awards|2019 Latin Grammys]] for his collaboration with [[Juanes]] on \"[[Querer Mejor]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latingrammy.com/es/nominees|title=20a Entrega Anual del Latin GRAMMY|website=Latin GRAMMYs|language=es|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> Her second studio album, ''[[The Pains of Growing]]'' (2018), saw the moderate commercial success of the singles \"[[Growing Pains (Alessia Cara song)|Growing Pains]]\" and \"[[Trust My Lonely]]\".\n\n==Life and career==\n=== 1996\u20132013: Early life ===\nAlessia Caracciolo is from [[Brampton]], [[Ontario]], where she attended [[Cardinal Ambrozic Catholic Secondary School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lhsimprint.com/arts-entertainment-and-reviews/2015/10/30/Alessia-Cara-review/|title=Alessia Cara Review|website=The Imprint|access-date=June 2, 2016}}</ref> Her family is from [[Calabria]]. Her father was born in Canada to Italian parents, and her mother is an Italian immigrant.<ref name=\"teenvogue\"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Nostro |first=Lauren |url=http://ca.complex.com/music/2015/07/alessia-cara-here-interview |title=Alessia Cara Interview |website=Ca.complex.com |date=July 10, 2015 |accessdate=December 23, 2015}}</ref> She can speak Italian.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-35240974|title=BBC Sound of 2016: Alessia Cara interview|publisher=BBC News|date=January 7, 2016}}</ref> As a child, she wrote poetry and did theatre.<ref name=FaderMayApr2015>{{cite magazine|last1=Tolentino|first1=Jia|title=Meet Alessia Cara, Alt-Pop's New Sweetheart|url=http://www.thefader.com/2015/05/27/interview-alessia-cara-alt-pops-new-sweetheart|accessdate=June 1, 2015|magazine=The Fader|date=May 2015}}</ref> She began playing guitar at the age of 10 and taught herself how to play various songs.<ref name=FaderMayApr2015/> At the age of 13, she began her own [[YouTube]] channel where she posted covers of songs that she performed.<ref name=FaderMayApr2015/>\n\n=== 2014\u20132017: Career beginnings and ''Know-It-All'' ===\n[[File:Alessia Cara press photo 2015.png|thumb|right|Promotional photograph of Cara from 2015]]\nIn 2014, she flew to U.S.A and signed a management deal with [[EP Entertainment]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6678428/alessia-cara-interview-drake-cosign-taylor-swift-know-it-all-album|title=Drake Co-Signed Singer Alessia Cara on Her Rising Fame: 'It's the Coolest Fluke Ever'|work=Billboard|access-date=October 2, 2018}}</ref><ref name=MTVHatesParties>{{cite news|last1=Linder|first1=Emilee|title=This New Song Is For Everyone Who Secretly Hates Parties|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2144584/alessia-here/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|publisher=MTV|date=April 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Carvell|first1=Josh|title=Fresher Sounds|url=http://www.thenationalstudent.com/Music/2015-05-05/fresher_sounds_05/05/2015.html|accessdate=May 12, 2015|publisher=The National Student|date=May 5, 2015}}</ref> In April 2015, Cara released her official debut [[Single (music)|single]] through [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]].<ref>{{cite news|title=New Songs: Alessia Cara - Here|url=http://cutfromsteel.com/new-song-alessia-cara-here/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|publisher=Cut from Steel|date=May 4, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150507192052/http://cutfromsteel.com/new-song-alessia-cara-here/|archive-date=May 7, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Titled \"[[Here (Alessia Cara song)|Here]]\", it was described by [[MTV]] as \"a song for everyone who secretly hates parties.\"<ref name=\"MTVHatesParties\" /> Produced by [[Pop & Oak]] and [[Sebastian Kole]], the song is her personal experience with going to a party and being super uncomfortable at it.<ref name=\"FaderCover\" /> On May 5, 2015, the song was chosen as the \"can't-miss\" track by ''Spin'',<ref name=\"SPINTopPick\" /> as well as being listed as a \"must hear song\" by ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]''.<ref name=\"CosmoMustHear2\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/music/news/a39893/best-songs-miranda-lambert-ciara-missy-elliott/|title=The 8 Songs You Need to Hear This Week|last1=Thompson|first1=Eliza|date=May 1, 2015|accessdate=May 12, 2015|work=Cosmopolitan}}</ref> The song was also named one of the best Canadian songs of April by ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]''<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Zorgel|first1=Aaron|title=Northern Touch: The Best Canadian Songs of April|url=http://ca.complex.com/music/2015/04/best-canadian-songs-april/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|magazine=Complex|date=April 30, 2015}}</ref> and included on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'}}s \"20 Pop Songs You Need For Your Summer Playlist\" in June 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lipshutz|first1=Jason|title=20 Pop Songs You Need For Your Summer Playlist|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6597748/20-summer-pop-songs-playlist-you-need-2015|website=Billboard.com|date=June 11, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' later ranked \"Here\" at number 21 on its year-end list of the 50 best songs of 2015.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/50-best-songs-of-2015-20151203/titus-andronicus-dimed-out-20151203|title=50 Best Songs of 2015|magazine=Billboard.com}}</ref> On July 29, 2015, Cara made her television debut on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Alessia Cara Makes TV Debut Playing 'Here' With the Roots on 'Fallon|url=http://www.spin.com/2015/07/alessia-cara-here-jimmy-fallon-roots|last=Unterberger|first=Andrew|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|publisher=[[SpinMedia]]|date=July 30, 2015|accessdate=August 19, 2015}}</ref> \"Here\" then received a nomination for \"Original Song\" at the [[Streamy Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|title=5th Annual Nominees|url=http://www.streamys.org/nominees-winners/5th-annual-nominees-winners/|accessdate=August 24, 2015|publisher=Streamy Awards|date=August 12, 2015}}</ref> She released the EP ''[[Four Pink Walls (EP)|Four Pink Walls]]'', containing five songs, including her debut single. Her debut album, ''[[Know-It-All]]'', was released on November 13, 2015.<ref>Ward, Kat [http://www.papermag.com/2015/09/alessia_cara_four_pink_walls_here.php Alessia Cara: The Budding Pop Star Who's Making Introversion Cool] ''Paper Magazine''. September 9, 2015</ref>\n\nFrom January to April 2016, Cara embarked on her first headlining tour, the \"Know-It-All Tour,\" performing in various US and Canadian cities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2015/11/alessia-cara-announces-north-american-tour/|title=Alessia Cara announces North American tour|date=November 16, 2015}}</ref> She was short-listed for the BBC Music [[Sound of...]] award for 2016 and finished as the runner-up.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-35253690|title=Jack Garratt tops BBC Sound of 2016 list|date=January 8, 2016}}</ref> Cara was awarded as Breakthrough Artist of the Year at the 2016 [[Juno Award]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://junoawards.ca/nominees/|title=Nominees {{!}} The JUNO Awards|website=The JUNO Awards|language=en-US|access-date=March 8, 2016}}</ref> On March 7, 2016, Cara released a music video for \"[[Wild Things (song)|Wild Things]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-alessia-caras-youthful-celebratory-wild-things-video-20160307|title=Watch Alessia Cara's Youthful, Celebratory 'Wild Things' Video|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=March 8, 2016}}</ref> In April 2016, Cara was announced to be one of the supporting acts of British [[alternative rock]] band [[Coldplay]] in the European and North American legs of their [[A Head Full of Dreams Tour]], alongside British singer songwriter and [[Grammy Award|Grammy]] winner [[Foxes (singer)|Foxes]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Yoo|first1=Noah|title=Coldplay Expand U.S. Tour, Alessia Cara to Join|url=http://pitchfork.com/news/64672-coldplay-expand-us-tour-alessia-cara-to-join/|website=[[Pitchfork Media|Pitchfork]]|publisher=[[Cond\u00e9 Nast]]|accessdate=April 9, 2016|date=April 8, 2016}}</ref> On June 23, 2016, Cara was featured in a re-released version of the song \"[[Wild (Troye Sivan song)|Wild]]\" by [[Troye Sivan]]. The music video was released on July 22, 2016.<ref>{{Citation|last=TroyeSivanVEVO|title=Troye Sivan - WILD (Official Video) ft. Alessia Cara|date=July 22, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_8G4oaOxyxk|access-date=November 14, 2018}}</ref> She played [[Glastonbury Festival]] on June 24, 2016, in the John Peel tent. The music video for Cara's single \"[[How Far I'll Go]]\", from the [[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]] film ''[[Moana (2016 film)|Moana]]'', was released on November 3, 2016, and since then has received over 230 million views on [[YouTube]].<ref>Brittany Spanos, [https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-alessia-caras-gorgeous-beach-set-how-far-ill-go-video-w448538 \"Watch Alessia Cara's Gorgeous, Beach-Set 'How Far I'll Go' Video,\"] ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', November 3, 2016.</ref> The song was written by [[Lin-Manuel Miranda]], produced by [[Pop & Oak|Oak Felder]], and the video was directed by [[Aya Tanimura]].<ref>Ashley Lee, [http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7565495/alessia-cara-how-far-ill-go-music-video-moana \"'Moana': Alessia Cara Sings Lin-Manuel Miranda's Anthem 'How Far I'll Go' in New Music Video\"], ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', November 3, 2016.</ref> On December 15, 2016, Cara released a music video for \"Seventeen.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7625271/alessia-cara-seventeen-video|title=Alessia Cara Grows Up in New 'Seventeen' Video: Watch|date=December 15, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161216094951/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7625271/alessia-cara-seventeen-video|archive-date=December 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nCara performed as the musical guest on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' on February 4, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tarnoff|first1=Brooke|title=Watch How Far Alessia Cara Did Go on 'Saturday Night Live'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7678027/alessia-cara-saturday-night-live|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=February 23, 2017}}</ref> On April 18, 2017, the music video of the song \"[[Stay (Zedd and Alessia Cara song)|Stay]]\" by [[Zedd]] featuring Cara was released. Cara featured on the song \"[[1-800-273-8255 (song)|1-800-273-8255]]\" from [[Logic (rapper)|Logic]]'s ''[[Everybody (Logic album)|Everybody]]'' album. The song was released as a single on April 28, 2017 and also features American singer-songwriter [[Khalid (singer)|Khalid]]. Cara also made an appearance in the video, which was released on August 17, 2017.<ref>{{Citation|last=LogicVEVO|title=Logic - 1-800-273-8255 ft. Alessia Cara, Khalid|date=August 17, 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kb24RrHIbFk|access-date=November 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== 2018\u2013present: ''The Pains of Growing'' and ''This Summer'' ===\n[[File:Alessia Cara performing in Sydney.jpg|thumb|right|Cara performing in Sydney, Australia in 2018]]\nOn January 28, 2018, Cara was named the Best New Artist at the [[60th Annual Grammy Awards|2018 Grammy Awards]], making her the first Canadian artist to win this award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/grammys-2018-alessia-cara-wins-best-new-artist/|title=Grammys 2018: Alessia Cara Wins Best New Artist|website=Pitchfork.com}}</ref> On June 1, 2018, Cara released a teaser video following a week of cryptic [[Twitter]] posts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1002588132511010817|title=ac on Twitter|website=Twitter.com|access-date=June 11, 2018}}</ref> On June 9, she posted lyrics to a new song on her social media accounts for fans to piece together. Once completed, she announced the single's cover and name on June 11.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/alessia_cara_teases_new_single_with_lyric_guessing_game|title=Alessia Cara Teases New Single \"Growing Pains\" with Lyric Guessing Game|website=Exclaim.ca|language=en|access-date=June 11, 2018}}</ref> The single, entitled \"[[Growing Pains (Alessia Cara song)|Growing Pains]]\", was released on June 15, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8460554/alessia-cara-announces-growing-pains-first-song-off-sophomore-album|title=Alessia Cara Announces 'Growing Pains,' First Song Off Her Sophomore Album|work=Billboard|access-date=June 13, 2018}}</ref> Its music video was released on June 20, 2018,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8461933/alessia-cara-video-growing-pains|title=Alessia Cara Drops Dystopian 'Growing Pains' Music Video: Watch|work=Billboard|access-date=June 23, 2018}}</ref> and was nominated for Best Cinematography at the 2018 [[MTV Video Music Award|MTV VMAS]].\n\nIn 2018, Cara covered the [[Elton John]] song [[I Guess That's Why They Call It the Blues|\"I Guess That's Why They Call it the Blues\"]] on his tribute album [[Revamp & Restoration|''Revamp'']].\n\nOn July 10, 2018, Cara announced that she would be releasing a song she made in her basement, written and produced by her, the next day, as a small gift for her birthday. The single, titled \"A Little More\", was released on July 11, 2018, with the music video also released the same day.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Thompson|first=Rita |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8464815/alessia-cara-new-song-a-little-more|title=Alessia Cara Announces New Song 'A Little More,' to Be Released on Her Birthday|date=July 10, 2018|work=Billboard|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Bargiela|first=Sara |url=https://www.entertainment-focus.com/music-section/music-news/alessia-cara-reveals-new-video-for-a-little-more/|title=Alessia Cara reveals new video for A Little More|date=July 12, 2018|work=Entertainment Focus|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BlDrCQmHOik/|title=ALESSIA CARA on Instagram: \"I made a song in my basement and thought I'd release it tomorrow as a small gift for my birthday. \"a little more\"\u2014written & produced by me....\"|website=Instagram.com|access-date=July 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Alessia Cara- A Little More (Official Video)|date=July 11, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WqxYyUR72jU|access-date=July 11, 2018}}</ref> On September 29, 2018, the [[Canadian Football League]] announced that Cara would be the halftime performer at the [[106th Grey Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/alessia-cara-grey-cup-1.4844604|title=Alessia Cara to headline 2018 Grey Cup halftime show|work=CBC News|access-date=October 2, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> In October 2018, she collaborated with Italian singer [[Eros Ramazzotti]] for the song \"Vale per sempre\", from the album ''[[Vita ce n'\u00e8]]''.<ref name=\"The 105\">{{cite web|url=https://www.105.net/news/music-biz/252935/eros-ramazzotti-ecco-il-video-di-vita-ce-n-e.html|title=Eros Ramazzotti, ecco il video di 'Vita ce n'\u00e8'|publisher=[[Radio 105 Network|Radio 105]]|language=Italian|date=October 19, 2018|accessdate=November 4, 2018}}</ref> On October 5, 2018, Cara released another song, entitled \"[[Trust My Lonely]]\". A music video for the song was released the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2018/9/28/alessia-cara-announces-new-song-trust-my-lonely-via-bizarre.html|title=Alessia Cara announces new song, \"Trust My Lonely,\" via bizarre Instagram video|work=[[ABC News Radio]]|last=Dresdale|first=Andrea|date=September 28, 2018|accessdate=September 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Glicksman|first=Josh |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8478701/alessia-cara-trust-my-lonely-video|title=Alessia Cara Drops Colorful Video for 'Trust My Lonely': Watch|date=October 8, 2018|work=Billboard|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref> On November 8, 2018, a music video for the song \"Babies\" by [[Kyle (musician)|Kyle]] featuring Cara was released.<ref>{{Citation|last=SuperDuperKyle|title=KYLE - Babies feat. Alessia Cara [Official Music Video]|date=November 8, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dl3JWhxOR6c|access-date=November 14, 2018}}</ref> On November 13, 2018, Cara released another song, entitled \"Not Today.\"<ref>{{Citation|last=AlessiaCaraVEVO|title=Alessia Cara - Not Today (Lyric Video)|date=November 13, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=60zHeOpc8sU|access-date=November 14, 2018}}</ref> The release date coincides with the three-year anniversary of the release of her debut album. Cara's second studio album, ''[[The Pains of Growing]]'', was released on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2018/10/alessia-cara-unveils-the-pains-of-growing-album-art-tracklist/|title=Alessia Cara Unveils The Pains of Growing Album Art, Tracklist|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|last=Arcand|first=Rob|date=October 26, 2018|accessdate=October 26, 2018}}</ref> It reached number 1 on the US iTunes Pop Chart less than two hours after its release. Despite its position on iTunes the album debuted at number 71 on the ''Billboard'' 200 albums Chart; 62 positions lower than her debut in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacworld/status/1068392629933608960|title=Alessia Cara World on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=November 30, 2018|language=en}}</ref> \"[[Out of Love (song)|Out of Love]]\" was eventually serviced to [[contemporary hit radio]] as the album's third single in January 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|publisher=All Access Media Group|accessdate=February 3, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190127025730/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archivedate=January 27, 2019}}</ref> Cara also collaborated with [[Alec Benjamin]] on \"[[Let Me Down Slowly]]\", which was released on January 7, 2019. On February 21, Cara announced she would join [[Shawn Mendes]] as the opening act on his [[Shawn Mendes: The Tour|self-titled world tour]] for the European, United Kingdom, and United States legs.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1098675382298071041|title=Alessia Cara on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=March 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/ShawnMendes/status/1098674680582598660|title= Shawn Mendes on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=March 13, 2019}}</ref> In May, she headlined \"[[The Pains of Growing Tour]],\" visiting Canadian cities in the month of May.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kiss925.com/2019/01/31/alessia-cara-tour/|title=Alessia Cara Announces 'The Pains of Growing' 2019 Canadian Tour!|website=Kiss925.com|accessdate=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, Cara announced the release of an EP, ''[[This Summer (EP)|This Summer]]'', with tracks to be issued \"every couple of weeks\" leading up to its release on September 6, 2019.<ref>{{cite|url=http://www.umusic.ca/press-releases/alessia-cara-surprises-fans-with-new-song-ready-off-of-forthcoming-ep-this-summer-out-september-6th/|title=ALESSIA CARA SURPRISES FANS WITH NEW SONG \u201cREADY\u201d OFF FORTHCOMING EP, THIS SUMMER, OUT SEPTEMBER 6|website=[[Umusic]]|date=July 22, 2019|accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref> She also announced that she will be adding a new leg of \"[[The Pains of Growing Tour]],\" visiting various US cities in October and November.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.axs.com/alessia-cara-announces-fall-2019-tour-and-new-ep-this-summer-138260|title=Alessia Cara announces fall 2019 tour and new EP, 'This Summer'}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2019/7/22/alessia-cara-releases-new-single-ready-announces-fall-tour-d.html|title=Alessia Cara releases new single \"Ready,\" announces fall tour dates - Music News - ABC News Radio|website=Abcnewsradioonline.com|accessdate=2020-04-13}}</ref> The first single of the EP, \"[[Ready (Alessia Cara song)|Ready]]\", was released on July 22.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=alessiacara|number=1151899912797401088|title=caught the writing bug out of the blue and made an EP. it's called This Summer. I'll be releasing a new track every couple of weeks until its release. the first song, Ready, will be out July 22nd.|date=July 18, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8521055/alessia-cara-announces-new-this-summer-ep-first-single-ready|title=Alessia Cara Announces New 'This Summer' EP & First Single 'Ready'|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=July 18, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019}}</ref> The second single, \"[[Rooting for You (Alessia Cara song)|Rooting for You]]\", was released on August 9.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1159176193385611265|title=Rooting For You. This Friday.pic.twitter.com/cLGVbr7MML|last=ac|date=August 7, 2019|website=Twitter.com|language=en|access-date=August 9, 2019}}</ref> The third single, \"Okay Okay\", was released on August 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B1buLiXH4LS/|title=ALESSIA CARA on Instagram: \"OKAY OKAY. this Friday.\"|via=Instagram||access-date=August 29, 2019}}</ref> The fourth single, \"October\", was released on September 3.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3137815/alessia-cara-october-song/|title=Alessia Cara Says Goodbye To An Unforgettable Tour On 'October'|first=Trey|last=Alston|website=MTV News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/Music/2019/09/03/Alessia-Cara-releases-new-song-October-from-upcoming-EP/8391567512581/|title=Alessia Cara releases new song 'October' from upcoming EP|website=Upi.com|accessdate=2020-04-13}}</ref> The music video for \"October\" was released on October 1, 2019.<ref>[https://wiky.com/news/articles/2019/oct/01/alessia-cara-documents-her-time-touring-with-shawn-mendes-in-october-music-video/942954/] {{dead link|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n\nShe featured Bastille in their song \"[[Another Place (Bastille and Alessia Cara song)|Another Place]]\" with a music video released on November 1.\n\n==Personal life==\nCara was in a relationship with singer [[Kevin Garrett (musician)|Kevin Garrett]] from 2016 to 2018. Cara has revealed on separate occasions that she experiences [[synesthesia]]<ref>{{Citation|last=Umusic|title=Alessia Cara Discusses Having Synesthesia {{!}} UMUSIC 5|date=September 20, 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zEC4mwDNIsw|access-date=July 3, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=AlessiaCaraVEVO|title=Alessia Cara - Painting|date=December 1, 2015|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AoRWdcowK1E|access-date=July 3, 2019}}</ref> and has [[keratosis pilaris]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1051701843989028865|title=I actually have keratosis pilaris (skin condition). used to be on my face but now it\u2019s only on parts of my body so there\u2019s a fun fact you didn\u2019t ask for|date=October 14, 2018|website=Twitter.com|language=en|access-date=July 3, 2019}}</ref> and [[alopecia areata]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1172318051670228993|title=alopecia kicked in it\u2019s more now!|website=Twitter.com|date=September 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1172320273221050368|title=genetic hairloss. had it since I was like 14 but mine comes in better / worse waves! I\u2019m lucky I got the frizz lol|website=Twitter.com|date=September 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\nCara is a [[Pop music|pop]],<ref name=\"allmusic\"/><ref name=\"indie\"/><ref name=\"wild things\"/> [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]],<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite work| title = Alessia Cara {{!}} Biography, Albums, Streaming Links |publisher= Allmusic| first= Andrew | last= Kellman |date=  |url= https://www.allmusic.com/artist/alessia-cara-mn0003396562 |accessdate= January 28, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"indie\"/> [[alternative R&B]],<ref>{{cite work| title = Bestival Cheat Sheet: Hometown Heroes |work= Complex| first= Aaron | last= Zorgel |date= June 11, 2015 |url= http://www.complex.com/music/2015/06/bestival-cheat-sheet-hometown-heroes/alessia-cara |accessdate= January 28, 2018}}</ref> [[indie pop]]<ref name=\"indie\">{{cite work| title = 10 New Indie Pop Artists You Should Know |publisher= Odyssey| first= Brien | last= Miceli |date= October 6, 2015 |url= https://www.theodysseyonline.com/10-indie-pop-artists |accessdate= January 28, 2018}}</ref> and [[Soul music|soul]]<ref name=\"wild things\">{{cite work| title = Alessia Cara \"Wild Things\" |work= Exclaim!| first= Gregory | last= Adams |date= October 27, 2015 |url= http://exclaim.ca/music/article/alessia_cara-wild_things |accessdate= January 28, 2018}}</ref> singer.\n\nHer influences include [[Lauryn Hill]], [[Amy Winehouse]], [[Pink (singer)|Pink]], [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]],<ref>{{cite work| title = Alessia Cara's Empowering Journey: Lessons from Coldplay, Lauryn Hill, & Life |work= [[Rap-Up]]| first= Andres | last= Tardio |date= September 27, 2016 |url= http://www.rap-up.com/2016/09/27/alessia-cara-lessons-from-coldplay-lauryn-hill-life/ |accessdate= January 8, 2017}}</ref> [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] and [[Ed Sheeran]].<ref>{{cite work| title = Sound of BBC: 2nd Alessia Cara |publisher= [[BBC]] |date= July 16, 2014 |url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/558ttb4cX0DN2SfPVkbbLF5/2nd-alessia-cara |accessdate= January 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{main|Alessia Cara discography}}\n\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|-\n! width=\"20%\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! colspan=\"10\"| Best Charts Peak\n! width=\"15%\" rowspan=\"2\"| Sale\n! width=\"20%\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Certification]]\n|-\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref name=\"billboard1\">{{citar web |titulo=Alessia Cara - Chart history (Canada) |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/6592648/Alessia+Cara/chart?f=309 |publicado=Billboard.com |acessodata=22 de outubro de 2015}}</ref>\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br /><ref name=\"AUS\"/>\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[Tracklisten|DEN]]<br /><ref name=\"DEN\">{{citar web |url=http://danishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Alessia+Cara |titulo=Discography Alessia Cara |acessodata=8 de mar\u00e7o de 2017}}</ref>\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[GfK Entertainment Charts|GER]]<br /><ref name=\"GER\"/>\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[Irish Albums Chart|IRE]]<br /><ref name=\"IRE\">{{citar web |url=http://irish-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Alessia+Cara |titulo=Discography Alessia Cara |publicado=Irish Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[MegaCharts|NL]]<br /><ref name=\"NL\">{{citar web |url=http://dutchcharts.nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Alessia+Cara |titulo=Discografie Alessia Cara |publicado=Dutch Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[Official New Zealand Music Chart|NZ]]<br /><ref name=\"NZ\"/>\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br /><ref>{{citar web |url=http://www.sverigetopplistan.se/ |titulo=Archived copy |acessodata=11 de julho de 2014|urlmorta=yes |arquivourl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226154145/http://www.sverigetopplistan.se/ |arquivodata=26 de dezembro de 2015}}. Click on \"Veckans albumlista\".</ref>\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br /><ref name=\"UK\">Peaks in the UK:\n* All except noted: {{citar web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48259/alessia-cara/ |titulo=Alessia Cara |publicado=[[Official Charts Company]] |acessodata=22 de janeiro de 2016}}\n* \"Wild Things\": {{citar web |titulo=CHART: CLUK Update 19.03.2016 (wk11) |url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/160319cluk.txt |publicado=[[UK Singles Chart]] |acessodata=1 de abril de 2016}}</ref>\n! width=\"20\"| <small>[[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=\"billboard2\">{{citar web |titulo=Alessia Cara - Chart history \u2013 Billboard 200 (US) |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/6592648/Alessia+Cara/chart?f=305 |publicado=Billboard.com |acessodata=22 de outubro de 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Know-It-All]]''\n* Released: November 13, 2015\n* Label: [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]]\n* Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], Download digital\n|align=\"center\"| 8\n|align=\"center\"| 16\n|align=\"center\"| 19\n|align=\"center\"| 99\n|align=\"center\"| 52\n|align=\"center\"| 34\n|align=\"center\"| 26\n|align=\"center\"| 21\n|align=\"center\"| 14\n|align=\"center\"| 9\n|\n* {{USA}}:      1 000 000\n* {{CAN}}:      100 000\n|\n* {{USA}}: {{Certification|silver}}<ref name=\"RIAA\">{{citar web |url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=Alessia+Cara#search_section |titulo=RIAA \u2013 Alessia Cara |publicado=[[Recording Industry Association of America]] |data=22 de maio de 2017 |acessodata=30 de maio de 2017}}</ref>\n* {{CAN}}: {{Certification|silver}}<ref name=\"MC\">{{citar web |url=https://musiccanada.com/gold-platinum/?fwp_gp_search=Alessia%20Cara |titulo=Gold/Platinum - Music Canada |publicado=[[Music Canada]] |acessodata=31 de julho de 2017}}</ref>\n* {{DNK}}: {{Certification|Gold}}<ref>{{citar web |url=http://ifpi.dk/?q=content/alessia-cara-know-it-all |titulo=Alessia Cara \"Know-It-All\" |publicado=[[IFPI Denmark]] |data=21 de mar\u00e7o de 2017 |acessodata=28 de mar\u00e7o de 2017 |l\u00edngua=da}}</ref>\n* {{UK}}: {{Certification|Silver}}\n|-\n| ''[[The Pains of Growing]]''\n* Released: November 30, 2018\n* Label: [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]]\n* Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], Download digital\n|align=\"center\"| 21\n|align=\"center\"| 76\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| 78\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| 71\n|\n* {{EUA}}: 13 000\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"14\" style=\"font-size:90%\" | \"\u2014\" indicates that the album didn't make on the musical chat or wasn't released on the territory.\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[The Willoughbys]]''\n|Jane Willoughby\n|Voice role\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Alessia Cara}}\n\nIn 2018, Cara became the first Canadian artist to ever win the [[Grammy Award for Best New Artist]].\nShe has also received nominations at the [[American Music Awards]] and [[Billboard Music Awards]], and won an [[iHeartRadio Music Award]], two [[Juno Awards]], two [[MTV Video Music Awards]], and an [[MTV Europe Music Award]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.alessiacara.com/}}\n* [http://www.defjam.com/artists/alessia-cara/ Def Jam Recordings profile for Alessia Cara]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm7487200/ Alessia Cara on the Internet Movie Database]\n{{Commons category|Alessia Cara}}\n\n{{Alessia Cara}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = [[List of awards and nominations received by Alessia Cara|Awards for Alessia Cara]]\n|list  = \n{{Grammy Award for Best New Artist}}\n{{MTV Video Music Award for Best Video with a Social Message}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cara, Alessia}}\n[[Category:Alessia Cara| ]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian singers]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian child singers]]\n[[Category:Canadian female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Canadian female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Calabrian descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian contemporary R&B singers]]\n[[Category:Canadian indie pop musicians]]\n[[Category:Canadian soul singers]]\n[[Category:Def Jam Recordings artists]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Juno Award for Breakthrough Artist of the Year winners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Brampton]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n[[Category:Juno Award for Pop Album of the Year winners]]\n[[Category:People with synesthesia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{short description|Canadian singer}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Alessia Cara\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Alessia Caracciolo\n| image            = Alessia Cara at the Capital Pride Concert.jpeg\n| caption          = Cara performing in 2018\n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1996|7|11}}<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbc.ca/radio/q/blog/12-things-you-need-to-know-about-alessia-cara-canada-s-first-ever-best-new-artist-grammy-winner-1.4509275 |title=12 things you need to know about Alessia Cara, Canada's first-ever best new artist Grammy winner |last=Van Evra |first=Jennifer |date=January 29, 2018 |publisher=[[CBC Radio]] |access-date=July 10, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Brampton]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| origin           = [[Brampton]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[alternative R&B]]\n* [[indie pop]]\n* [[Soul music|soul]]\n}}\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* songwriter\n* multi-instrumentalist\n}}\n| instrument       = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* guitar\n* ukulele\n* piano\n}}\n| years_active     = 2014\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[EP Entertainment|EP]]\n* [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]]<ref name=NYTimes19May>{{cite news|last1=Caramanica|first1=Jon|title=Alessia Cara Speaks Up for the Outsiders on 'Here'|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/20/arts/music/alessia-cara-speaks-up-for-the-outsiders-on-here.html|accessdate=June 1, 2015|newspaper=The New York Times|date=May 19, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Universal Music Canada]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/7767524/universal-music-canada-relocating-rock-star-building-toronto|title=Universal Music Canada Relocating To 'Rock Star Building' in Downtown Toronto|date=April 19, 2017|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n}}\n| associated_acts  = [[Pop & Oak]]\n| website          = {{URL|alessiacara.com}}\n| image_size       = 200px\n}}\n\n'''Alessia Caracciolo''' (born July 11, 1996), known professionally as '''Alessia Cara''' ({{IPAc-en|\u0259|'|l|\u025b|s|i|\u0259|_|'|k|\u0251\u02d0|r|\u0259|}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/a34453/celebrity-name-pronunciations/|title=11 Celeb Names You're Totally Pronouncing Wrong|work=[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]|date=July 31, 2017|accessdate=November 19, 2017}}</ref>), is a Canadian singer, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist.<ref name=\"teenvogue\">{{cite magazine|last1=Thurmond|first1=Alexandra|title=Sound Scout: Alessia Cara is the 18-year-old Singer-Songwriter We Cant Get Enough Of|url=http://www.teenvogue.com/entertainment/music/2015-05/sound-scout-alessia-cara-interview|accessdate=June 1, 2015|magazine=Teen Vogue|date=May 2015}}</ref><ref name=SPINTopPick>{{cite magazine|title=SPIN Singles Mix: Titus Andronicus, Vince Staples, Miguel, and More|url=http://www.spin.com/2015/05/singles-mix-titus-andronicus-vince-staples-miguel/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|magazine=SPIN Magazine|date=May 5, 2015}}</ref> After producing acoustic covers, she signed with [[EP Entertainment]] and [[Def Jam Recordings]] in 2014 and released her debut single the following year. \"[[Here (Alessia Cara song)|Here]]\" reached number 19 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] chart and was a [[sleeper hit]] in the United States, peaking at number 5 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart.<ref name=\"FaderCover\">{{cite magazine|last1=Zeichner|first1=Naomi|title=Every Introvert Needs To See This Song|url=https://www.thefader.com/2015/04/27/alessia-here|accessdate=May 12, 2015|magazine=The Fader|date=April 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Lewis|first1=Brittany|title=Alessia \"Here\" (New Music)|url=http://globalgrind.com/2015/04/28/alessia-here-new-music/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|publisher=Global Grind|date=April 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nCara's debut studio album, ''[[Know-It-All]]'' (2015), reached number 8 on the [[Canadian Albums Chart]] and number 9 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart in the United States. The album's third single, \"[[Scars to Your Beautiful]]\", reached number 8 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 in 2016. In 2017, Cara collaborated with DJ and producer [[Zedd]] to create the single \"[[Stay (Zedd and Alessia Cara song)|Stay]]\", and with rapper [[Logic (rapper)|Logic]] to feature in his song {{nowrap|\"[[1-800-273-8255 (song)|1-800-273-8255]]\"}}. Cara has received nominations for four [[Grammy Awards]], including a win for [[Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/grammys-2018-alessia-cara-wins-best-new-artist/|title=Grammys 2018: Alessia Cara Wins Best New Artist |website=Pitchfork.com|language=en|access-date=January 29, 2018}}</ref> She was nominated for [[Latin Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]] and [[Latin Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]] at the [[20th Annual Latin Grammy Awards|2019 Latin Grammys]] for his collaboration with [[Juanes]] on \"[[Querer Mejor]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latingrammy.com/es/nominees|title=20a Entrega Anual del Latin GRAMMY|website=Latin GRAMMYs|language=es|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> Her second studio album, ''[[The Pains of Growing]]'' (2018), saw the moderate commercial success of the singles \"[[Growing Pains (Alessia Cara song)|Growing Pains]]\" and \"[[Trust My Lonely]]\".\n\n==Life and career==\n=== 1996\u20132013: Early life ===\nAlessia Caracciolo is from [[Brampton]], [[Ontario]], where she attended [[Cardinal Ambrozic Catholic Secondary School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lhsimprint.com/arts-entertainment-and-reviews/2015/10/30/Alessia-Cara-review/|title=Alessia Cara Review|website=The Imprint|access-date=June 2, 2016}}</ref> Her family is from [[Calabria]]. Her father was born in Canada to Italian parents, and her mother is an Italian immigrant.<ref name=\"teenvogue\"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Nostro |first=Lauren |url=http://ca.complex.com/music/2015/07/alessia-cara-here-interview |title=Alessia Cara Interview |website=Ca.complex.com |date=July 10, 2015 |accessdate=December 23, 2015}}</ref> She can speak Italian.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-35240974|title=BBC Sound of 2016: Alessia Cara interview|publisher=BBC News|date=January 7, 2016}}</ref> As a child, she wrote poetry and did theatre.<ref name=FaderMayApr2015>{{cite magazine|last1=Tolentino|first1=Jia|title=Meet Alessia Cara, Alt-Pop's New Sweetheart|url=http://www.thefader.com/2015/05/27/interview-alessia-cara-alt-pops-new-sweetheart|accessdate=June 1, 2015|magazine=The Fader|date=May 2015}}</ref> She began playing guitar at the age of 10 and taught herself how to play various songs.<ref name=FaderMayApr2015/> At the age of 13, she began her own [[YouTube]] channel where she posted covers of songs that she performed.<ref name=FaderMayApr2015/>\n\n=== 2014\u20132017: Career beginnings and ''Know-It-All'' ===\n[[File:Alessia Cara press photo 2015.png|thumb|right|Promotional photograph of Cara from 2015]]\nIn 2014, she flew to U.S.A and signed a management deal with [[EP Entertainment]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6678428/alessia-cara-interview-drake-cosign-taylor-swift-know-it-all-album|title=Drake Co-Signed Singer Alessia Cara on Her Rising Fame: 'It's the Coolest Fluke Ever'|work=Billboard|access-date=October 2, 2018}}</ref><ref name=MTVHatesParties>{{cite news|last1=Linder|first1=Emilee|title=This New Song Is For Everyone Who Secretly Hates Parties|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2144584/alessia-here/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|publisher=MTV|date=April 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Carvell|first1=Josh|title=Fresher Sounds|url=http://www.thenationalstudent.com/Music/2015-05-05/fresher_sounds_05/05/2015.html|accessdate=May 12, 2015|publisher=The National Student|date=May 5, 2015}}</ref> In April 2015, Cara released her official debut [[Single (music)|single]] through [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]].<ref>{{cite news|title=New Songs: Alessia Cara - Here|url=http://cutfromsteel.com/new-song-alessia-cara-here/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|publisher=Cut from Steel|date=May 4, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150507192052/http://cutfromsteel.com/new-song-alessia-cara-here/|archive-date=May 7, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Titled \"[[Here (Alessia Cara song)|Here]]\", it was described by [[MTV]] as \"a song for everyone who secretly hates parties.\"<ref name=\"MTVHatesParties\" /> Produced by [[Pop & Oak]] and [[Sebastian Kole]], the song is her personal experience with going to a party and being super uncomfortable at it.<ref name=\"FaderCover\" /> On May 5, 2015, the song was chosen as the \"can't-miss\" track by ''Spin'',<ref name=\"SPINTopPick\" /> as well as being listed as a \"must hear song\" by ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]''.<ref name=\"CosmoMustHear2\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/music/news/a39893/best-songs-miranda-lambert-ciara-missy-elliott/|title=The 8 Songs You Need to Hear This Week|last1=Thompson|first1=Eliza|date=May 1, 2015|accessdate=May 12, 2015|work=Cosmopolitan}}</ref> The song was also named one of the best Canadian songs of April by ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]''<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Zorgel|first1=Aaron|title=Northern Touch: The Best Canadian Songs of April|url=http://ca.complex.com/music/2015/04/best-canadian-songs-april/|accessdate=May 12, 2015|magazine=Complex|date=April 30, 2015}}</ref> and included on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'}}s \"20 Pop Songs You Need For Your Summer Playlist\" in June 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lipshutz|first1=Jason|title=20 Pop Songs You Need For Your Summer Playlist|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6597748/20-summer-pop-songs-playlist-you-need-2015|website=Billboard.com|date=June 11, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' later ranked \"Here\" at number 21 on its year-end list of the 50 best songs of 2015.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/50-best-songs-of-2015-20151203/titus-andronicus-dimed-out-20151203|title=50 Best Songs of 2015|magazine=Billboard.com}}</ref> On July 29, 2015, Cara made her television debut on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Alessia Cara Makes TV Debut Playing 'Here' With the Roots on 'Fallon|url=http://www.spin.com/2015/07/alessia-cara-here-jimmy-fallon-roots|last=Unterberger|first=Andrew|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|publisher=[[SpinMedia]]|date=July 30, 2015|accessdate=August 19, 2015}}</ref> \"Here\" then received a nomination for \"Original Song\" at the [[Streamy Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|title=5th Annual Nominees|url=http://www.streamys.org/nominees-winners/5th-annual-nominees-winners/|accessdate=August 24, 2015|publisher=Streamy Awards|date=August 12, 2015}}</ref> She released the EP ''[[Four Pink Walls (EP)|Four Pink Walls]]'', containing five songs, including her debut single. Her debut album, ''[[Know-It-All]]'', was released on November 13, 2015.<ref>Ward, Kat [http://www.papermag.com/2015/09/alessia_cara_four_pink_walls_here.php Alessia Cara: The Budding Pop Star Who's Making Introversion Cool] ''Paper Magazine''. September 9, 2015</ref>\n\nFrom January to April 2016, Cara embarked on her first headlining tour, the \"Know-It-All Tour,\" performing in various US and Canadian cities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2015/11/alessia-cara-announces-north-american-tour/|title=Alessia Cara announces North American tour|date=November 16, 2015}}</ref> She was short-listed for the BBC Music [[Sound of...]] award for 2016 and finished as the runner-up.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-35253690|title=Jack Garratt tops BBC Sound of 2016 list|date=January 8, 2016}}</ref> Cara was awarded as Breakthrough Artist of the Year at the 2016 [[Juno Award]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://junoawards.ca/nominees/|title=Nominees {{!}} The JUNO Awards|website=The JUNO Awards|language=en-US|access-date=March 8, 2016}}</ref> On March 7, 2016, Cara released a music video for \"[[Wild Things (song)|Wild Things]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-alessia-caras-youthful-celebratory-wild-things-video-20160307|title=Watch Alessia Cara's Youthful, Celebratory 'Wild Things' Video|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=March 8, 2016}}</ref> In April 2016, Cara was announced to be one of the supporting acts of British [[alternative rock]] band [[Coldplay]] in the European and North American legs of their [[A Head Full of Dreams Tour]], alongside British singer songwriter and [[Grammy Award|Grammy]] winner [[Foxes (singer)|Foxes]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Yoo|first1=Noah|title=Coldplay Expand U.S. Tour, Alessia Cara to Join|url=http://pitchfork.com/news/64672-coldplay-expand-us-tour-alessia-cara-to-join/|website=[[Pitchfork Media|Pitchfork]]|publisher=[[Cond\u00e9 Nast]]|accessdate=April 9, 2016|date=April 8, 2016}}</ref> On June 23, 2016, Cara was featured in a re-released version of the song \"[[Wild (Troye Sivan song)|Wild]]\" by [[Troye Sivan]]. The music video was released on July 22, 2016.<ref>{{Citation|last=TroyeSivanVEVO|title=Troye Sivan - WILD (Official Video) ft. Alessia Cara|date=July 22, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_8G4oaOxyxk|access-date=November 14, 2018}}</ref> She played [[Glastonbury Festival]] on June 24, 2016, in the John Peel tent. The music video for Cara's single \"[[How Far I'll Go]]\", from the [[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]] film ''[[Moana (2016 film)|Moana]]'', was released on November 3, 2016, and since then has received over 230 million views on [[YouTube]].<ref>Brittany Spanos, [https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-alessia-caras-gorgeous-beach-set-how-far-ill-go-video-w448538 \"Watch Alessia Cara's Gorgeous, Beach-Set 'How Far I'll Go' Video,\"] ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', November 3, 2016.</ref> The song was written by [[Lin-Manuel Miranda]], produced by [[Pop & Oak|Oak Felder]], and the video was directed by [[Aya Tanimura]].<ref>Ashley Lee, [http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7565495/alessia-cara-how-far-ill-go-music-video-moana \"'Moana': Alessia Cara Sings Lin-Manuel Miranda's Anthem 'How Far I'll Go' in New Music Video\"], ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', November 3, 2016.</ref> On December 15, 2016, Cara released a music video for \"Seventeen.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7625271/alessia-cara-seventeen-video|title=Alessia Cara Grows Up in New 'Seventeen' Video: Watch|date=December 15, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161216094951/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7625271/alessia-cara-seventeen-video|archive-date=December 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nCara performed as the musical guest on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' on February 4, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tarnoff|first1=Brooke|title=Watch How Far Alessia Cara Did Go on 'Saturday Night Live'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7678027/alessia-cara-saturday-night-live|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=February 23, 2017}}</ref> On April 18, 2017, the music video of the song \"[[Stay (Zedd and Alessia Cara song)|Stay]]\" by [[Zedd]] featuring Cara was released. Cara featured on the song \"[[1-800-273-8255 (song)|1-800-273-8255]]\" from [[Logic (rapper)|Logic]]'s ''[[Everybody (Logic album)|Everybody]]'' album. The song was released as a single on April 28, 2017 and also features American singer-songwriter [[Khalid (singer)|Khalid]]. Cara also made an appearance in the video, which was released on August 17, 2017.<ref>{{Citation|last=LogicVEVO|title=Logic - 1-800-273-8255 ft. Alessia Cara, Khalid|date=August 17, 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kb24RrHIbFk|access-date=November 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== 2018\u2013present: ''The Pains of Growing'' and ''This Summer'' ===\n[[File:Alessia Cara performing in Sydney.jpg|thumb|right|Cara performing in Sydney, Australia in 2018]]\nOn January 28, 2018, Cara was named the Best New Artist at the [[60th Annual Grammy Awards|2018 Grammy Awards]], making her the first Canadian artist to win this award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/grammys-2018-alessia-cara-wins-best-new-artist/|title=Grammys 2018: Alessia Cara Wins Best New Artist|website=Pitchfork.com}}</ref> On June 1, 2018, Cara released a teaser video following a week of cryptic [[Twitter]] posts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1002588132511010817|title=ac on Twitter|website=Twitter.com|access-date=June 11, 2018}}</ref> On June 9, she posted lyrics to a new song on her social media accounts for fans to piece together. Once completed, she announced the single's cover and name on June 11.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/alessia_cara_teases_new_single_with_lyric_guessing_game|title=Alessia Cara Teases New Single \"Growing Pains\" with Lyric Guessing Game|website=Exclaim.ca|language=en|access-date=June 11, 2018}}</ref> The single, entitled \"[[Growing Pains (Alessia Cara song)|Growing Pains]]\", was released on June 15, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8460554/alessia-cara-announces-growing-pains-first-song-off-sophomore-album|title=Alessia Cara Announces 'Growing Pains,' First Song Off Her Sophomore Album|work=Billboard|access-date=June 13, 2018}}</ref> Its music video was released on June 20, 2018,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8461933/alessia-cara-video-growing-pains|title=Alessia Cara Drops Dystopian 'Growing Pains' Music Video: Watch|work=Billboard|access-date=June 23, 2018}}</ref> and was nominated for Best Cinematography at the 2018 [[MTV Video Music Award|MTV VMAS]].\n\nIn 2018, Cara covered the [[Elton John]] song [[I Guess That's Why They Call It the Blues|\"I Guess That's Why They Call it the Blues\"]] on his tribute album [[Revamp & Restoration|''Revamp'']].\n\nOn July 10, 2018, Cara announced that she would be releasing a song she made in her basement, written and produced by her, the next day, as a small gift for her birthday. The single, titled \"A Little More\", was released on July 11, 2018, with the music video also released the same day.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Thompson|first=Rita |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8464815/alessia-cara-new-song-a-little-more|title=Alessia Cara Announces New Song 'A Little More,' to Be Released on Her Birthday|date=July 10, 2018|work=Billboard|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Bargiela|first=Sara |url=https://www.entertainment-focus.com/music-section/music-news/alessia-cara-reveals-new-video-for-a-little-more/|title=Alessia Cara reveals new video for A Little More|date=July 12, 2018|work=Entertainment Focus|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BlDrCQmHOik/|title=ALESSIA CARA on Instagram: \"I made a song in my basement and thought I'd release it tomorrow as a small gift for my birthday. \"a little more\"\u2014written & produced by me....\"|website=Instagram.com|access-date=July 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Alessia Cara- A Little More (Official Video)|date=July 11, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WqxYyUR72jU|access-date=July 11, 2018}}</ref> On September 29, 2018, the [[Canadian Football League]] announced that Cara would be the halftime performer at the [[106th Grey Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/alessia-cara-grey-cup-1.4844604|title=Alessia Cara to headline 2018 Grey Cup halftime show|work=CBC News|access-date=October 2, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> In October 2018, she collaborated with Italian singer [[Eros Ramazzotti]] for the song \"Vale per sempre\", from the album ''[[Vita ce n'\u00e8]]''.<ref name=\"The 105\">{{cite web|url=https://www.105.net/news/music-biz/252935/eros-ramazzotti-ecco-il-video-di-vita-ce-n-e.html|title=Eros Ramazzotti, ecco il video di 'Vita ce n'\u00e8'|publisher=[[Radio 105 Network|Radio 105]]|language=Italian|date=October 19, 2018|accessdate=November 4, 2018}}</ref> On October 5, 2018, Cara released another song, entitled \"[[Trust My Lonely]]\". A music video for the song was released the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2018/9/28/alessia-cara-announces-new-song-trust-my-lonely-via-bizarre.html|title=Alessia Cara announces new song, \"Trust My Lonely,\" via bizarre Instagram video|work=[[ABC News Radio]]|last=Dresdale|first=Andrea|date=September 28, 2018|accessdate=September 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Glicksman|first=Josh |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8478701/alessia-cara-trust-my-lonely-video|title=Alessia Cara Drops Colorful Video for 'Trust My Lonely': Watch|date=October 8, 2018|work=Billboard|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref> On November 8, 2018, a music video for the song \"Babies\" by [[Kyle (musician)|Kyle]] featuring Cara was released.<ref>{{Citation|last=SuperDuperKyle|title=KYLE - Babies feat. Alessia Cara [Official Music Video]|date=November 8, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dl3JWhxOR6c|access-date=November 14, 2018}}</ref> On November 13, 2018, Cara released another song, entitled \"Not Today.\"<ref>{{Citation|last=AlessiaCaraVEVO|title=Alessia Cara - Not Today (Lyric Video)|date=November 13, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=60zHeOpc8sU|access-date=November 14, 2018}}</ref> The release date coincides with the three-year anniversary of the release of her debut album. Cara's second studio album, ''[[The Pains of Growing]]'', was released on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2018/10/alessia-cara-unveils-the-pains-of-growing-album-art-tracklist/|title=Alessia Cara Unveils The Pains of Growing Album Art, Tracklist|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|last=Arcand|first=Rob|date=October 26, 2018|accessdate=October 26, 2018}}</ref> It reached number 1 on the US iTunes Pop Chart less than two hours after its release. Despite its position on iTunes the album debuted at number 71 on the ''Billboard'' 200 albums Chart; 62 positions lower than her debut in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacworld/status/1068392629933608960|title=Alessia Cara World on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=November 30, 2018|language=en}}</ref> \"[[Out of Love (song)|Out of Love]]\" was eventually serviced to [[contemporary hit radio]] as the album's third single in January 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|publisher=All Access Media Group|accessdate=February 3, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190127025730/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archivedate=January 27, 2019}}</ref> Cara also collaborated with [[Alec Benjamin]] on \"[[Let Me Down Slowly]]\", which was released on January 7, 2019. On February 21, Cara announced she would join [[Shawn Mendes]] as the opening act on his [[Shawn Mendes: The Tour|self-titled world tour]] for the European, United Kingdom, and United States legs.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1098675382298071041|title=Alessia Cara on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=March 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/ShawnMendes/status/1098674680582598660|title= Shawn Mendes on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=March 13, 2019}}</ref> In May, she headlined \"[[The Pains of Growing Tour]],\" visiting Canadian cities in the month of May.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kiss925.com/2019/01/31/alessia-cara-tour/|title=Alessia Cara Announces 'The Pains of Growing' 2019 Canadian Tour!|website=Kiss925.com|accessdate=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, Cara announced the release of an EP, ''[[This Summer (EP)|This Summer]]'', with tracks to be issued \"every couple of weeks\" leading up to its release on September 6, 2019.<ref>{{cite|url=http://www.umusic.ca/press-releases/alessia-cara-surprises-fans-with-new-song-ready-off-of-forthcoming-ep-this-summer-out-september-6th/|title=ALESSIA CARA SURPRISES FANS WITH NEW SONG \u201cREADY\u201d OFF FORTHCOMING EP, THIS SUMMER, OUT SEPTEMBER 6|website=[[Umusic]]|date=July 22, 2019|accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref> She also announced that she will be adding a new leg of \"[[The Pains of Growing Tour]],\" visiting various US cities in October and November.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.axs.com/alessia-cara-announces-fall-2019-tour-and-new-ep-this-summer-138260|title=Alessia Cara announces fall 2019 tour and new EP, 'This Summer'}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2019/7/22/alessia-cara-releases-new-single-ready-announces-fall-tour-d.html|title=Alessia Cara releases new single \"Ready,\" announces fall tour dates - Music News - ABC News Radio|website=Abcnewsradioonline.com|accessdate=2020-04-13}}</ref> The first single of the EP, \"[[Ready (Alessia Cara song)|Ready]]\", was released on July 22.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=alessiacara|number=1151899912797401088|title=caught the writing bug out of the blue and made an EP. it's called This Summer. I'll be releasing a new track every couple of weeks until its release. the first song, Ready, will be out July 22nd.|date=July 18, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8521055/alessia-cara-announces-new-this-summer-ep-first-single-ready|title=Alessia Cara Announces New 'This Summer' EP & First Single 'Ready'|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=July 18, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019}}</ref> The second single, \"[[Rooting for You (Alessia Cara song)|Rooting for You]]\", was released on August 9.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1159176193385611265|title=Rooting For You. This Friday.pic.twitter.com/cLGVbr7MML|last=ac|date=August 7, 2019|website=Twitter.com|language=en|access-date=August 9, 2019}}</ref> The third single, \"Okay Okay\", was released on August 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B1buLiXH4LS/|title=ALESSIA CARA on Instagram: \"OKAY OKAY. this Friday.\"|via=Instagram||access-date=August 29, 2019}}</ref> The fourth single, \"October\", was released on September 3.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3137815/alessia-cara-october-song/|title=Alessia Cara Says Goodbye To An Unforgettable Tour On 'October'|first=Trey|last=Alston|website=MTV News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/Music/2019/09/03/Alessia-Cara-releases-new-song-October-from-upcoming-EP/8391567512581/|title=Alessia Cara releases new song 'October' from upcoming EP|website=Upi.com|accessdate=2020-04-13}}</ref> The music video for \"October\" was released on October 1, 2019.<ref>[https://wiky.com/news/articles/2019/oct/01/alessia-cara-documents-her-time-touring-with-shawn-mendes-in-october-music-video/942954/] {{dead link|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n\nShe featured Bastille in their song \"[[Another Place (Bastille and Alessia Cara song)|Another Place]]\" with a music video released on November 1.\n\n==Personal life==\nCara was in a relationship with singer [[Kevin Garrett (musician)|Kevin Garrett]] from 2016 to 2018. Cara has revealed on separate occasions that she experiences [[synesthesia]]<ref>{{Citation|last=Umusic|title=Alessia Cara Discusses Having Synesthesia {{!}} UMUSIC 5|date=September 20, 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zEC4mwDNIsw|access-date=July 3, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=AlessiaCaraVEVO|title=Alessia Cara - Painting|date=December 1, 2015|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AoRWdcowK1E|access-date=July 3, 2019}}</ref> and has [[keratosis pilaris]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1051701843989028865|title=I actually have keratosis pilaris (skin condition). used to be on my face but now it\u2019s only on parts of my body so there\u2019s a fun fact you didn\u2019t ask for|date=October 14, 2018|website=Twitter.com|language=en|access-date=July 3, 2019}}</ref> and [[alopecia areata]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1172318051670228993|title=alopecia kicked in it\u2019s more now!|website=Twitter.com|date=September 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alessiacara/status/1172320273221050368|title=genetic hairloss. had it since I was like 14 but mine comes in better / worse waves! I\u2019m lucky I got the frizz lol|website=Twitter.com|date=September 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\nCara is a [[Pop music|pop]],<ref name=\"allmusic\"/><ref name=\"indie\"/><ref name=\"wild things\"/> [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]],<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite work| title = Alessia Cara {{!}} Biography, Albums, Streaming Links |publisher= Allmusic| first= Andrew | last= Kellman |date=  |url= https://www.allmusic.com/artist/alessia-cara-mn0003396562 |accessdate= January 28, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"indie\"/> [[alternative R&B]],<ref>{{cite work| title = Bestival Cheat Sheet: Hometown Heroes |work= Complex| first= Aaron | last= Zorgel |date= June 11, 2015 |url= http://www.complex.com/music/2015/06/bestival-cheat-sheet-hometown-heroes/alessia-cara |accessdate= January 28, 2018}}</ref> [[indie pop]]<ref name=\"indie\">{{cite work| title = 10 New Indie Pop Artists You Should Know |publisher= Odyssey| first= Brien | last= Miceli |date= October 6, 2015 |url= https://www.theodysseyonline.com/10-indie-pop-artists |accessdate= January 28, 2018}}</ref> and [[Soul music|soul]]<ref name=\"wild things\">{{cite work| title = Alessia Cara \"Wild Things\" |work= Exclaim!| first= Gregory | last= Adams |date= October 27, 2015 |url= http://exclaim.ca/music/article/alessia_cara-wild_things |accessdate= January 28, 2018}}</ref> singer.\n\nHer influences include [[Lauryn Hill]], [[Amy Winehouse]], [[Pink (singer)|Pink]], [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]],<ref>{{cite work| title = Alessia Cara's Empowering Journey: Lessons from Coldplay, Lauryn Hill, & Life |work= [[Rap-Up]]| first= Andres | last= Tardio |date= September 27, 2016 |url= http://www.rap-up.com/2016/09/27/alessia-cara-lessons-from-coldplay-lauryn-hill-life/ |accessdate= January 8, 2017}}</ref> [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] and [[Ed Sheeran]].<ref>{{cite work| title = Sound of BBC: 2nd Alessia Cara |publisher= [[BBC]] |date= July 16, 2014 |url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/558ttb4cX0DN2SfPVkbbLF5/2nd-alessia-cara |accessdate= January 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{main|Alessia Cara discography}}\n\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|-\n! width=\"20%\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! colspan=\"10\"| Best Charts Peak\n! width=\"15%\" rowspan=\"2\"| Sale\n! width=\"20%\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Certification]]\n|-\n! width